      "message": "No worries. I have a few queries regarding the fuzz tests:\n1. Can I include these fuzz tests within the same ```fuzz.c``` file, or do I need to create a new file?\n2. The ```foreach_*()``` macros internally invoke the decode functions (unless init or other checks fail). However, do you want me to add separate fuzz tests for the decode methods? And also I hope a single fuzz test would be sufficient for covering both foreach macros.\n3. For the state effecter PDR, do you want the whole fuzz input treated as the raw PDR buffer, or a prefixed layout (e.g., a leading length, then the PDR bytes) so the fuzzer can vary pdr_size independently of the buffer contents?",
