      "writtenOn": "2026-05-19T06:42:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Can I include these fuzz tests within the same fuzz.c file, or do I need to create a new file?\n\nYes, for now, please include your fuzz test(s) in the same file. I plan to split it up in the future when it starts getting unwieldy.\n\n\u003e The foreach_*() macros internally invoke the decode functions (unless init or other checks fail). However, do you want me to add separate fuzz tests for the decode methods? And also I hope a single fuzz test would be sufficient for covering both foreach macros.\n\nA single fuzz test please. One that operates as if you were using the APIs in e.g. pldmd.\n\n\u003e For the state effecter PDR, do you want the whole fuzz input treated as the raw PDR buffer, or a prefixed layout (e.g., a leading length, then the PDR bytes) so the fuzzer can vary pdr_size independently of the buffer contents?\n\nlibfuzzer will vary the buffer lengths regardless. It\u0027s fine to use the content directly, though you will need to be careful about padding and alignment. Avoid casting. Use the msgbuf APIs to populate any relevant structs or extract parameters from the input buffer as you see fit.\n\nThe following might be instructive:\n\n- https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/libpldm/+/85298/23/tests/fuzz/fuzz.c\n- https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/libpldm/+/90357/1/tests/fuzz/fuzz.c",
      "parentUuid": "d9c8f178_68778262",
      "revId": "aa35aee7d3292aea48fbe265eecfaefb5010cac4",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
